structured.title: Discussion Of FBI Civil Rights Investigation
structured.overview: The speaker describes a man named Alex Pretty as someone who arrived at an ICE protest with ill intent. They are questioned about whether they would apologize if it were later determined that the man's civil rights were violated by an FBI investigation. The speaker repeatedly avoids committing to a hypothetical apology, emphasizing instead that they will wait for the investigation to conclude and apologizing only for being misunderstood.

## Description of Alex Pretty  
- Described as arriving at ICE protest with ill intent  
- Characterization tied to his behavior at the protest  

## Question on Civil Rights and Apology  
- Hypothetical: FBI found to violate his civil rights  
- Asked if he would apologize in that scenario  

## Response to Hypothetical  
- Refuses to commit on layered hypotheticals  
- Emphasizes waiting for investigation results  

## Next Steps  
- Await completion of FBI-related investigation  
- Revisit responsibility or apology after findings
